Two new members of the Financial Supervision Authority and the Financial Supervision Authority's council were approved, Mai Palmipuu and Veiko-Joel Kokk, who were nominated by me.
The Financial Supervision Authority's council has six members, three of whom are appointed by the Minister of Finance and three by the Bank of Estonia.
In addition, the Minister of Finance is a member by virtue of their position, and two members are appointed by the Minister of Finance, while the remaining members are appointed by the President of the Bank of Estonia, currently including Madis Müller, Maive Rute, and Rein Minko.
Until August, representatives of the Ministry of Finance were also present, including the former head of the Tax and Customs Board Valdur Laid and the Chancellor of the Ministry of Finance Veiko Tali, but their mandates have expired.
We also approved my proposal to increase the composition of the Census Commission, which is responsible for preparing and conducting the population census, by adding the Speaker of the Parliament or their appointed representative to ensure the Parliament's involvement in the process.
