This will save a significant amount of money.
We also amended the Statute of the Defense Forces, which concerns intelligence, giving the Intelligence Center the right to screen individuals who are being considered for secret cooperation, and specifying the tasks of the Air Force in organizing and supervising defense aviation.
In addition, we granted Estonian citizenship to two individuals and released thirty people from Estonian citizenship, mainly those who wish to obtain citizenship of another country.
And we refused to grant citizenship to three individuals because they had previously committed a crime or had numerous misdemeanors, and in such decisions the government first considers the background and nature of their crimes.
And then decides whether to grant them citizenship or not in exceptional cases, in this case citizenship was not granted to three individuals and we also received an overview of two unadopted directives. One of them is.
One was, what were the directives, one is the media, audiovisual media directive. There we have, there is, we need, this draft is actually prepared by the Ministry of Culture, but we need to look at this draft a little bit, because there is a risk that a censorship institution will gradually emerge in Estonia.
And, and the other one is.
What is this, the directive on the risk-free interest rate curve for volative adjustment? This is, this is a topic in the field of the Ministry of Finance and we confirmed the positions of the agriculture and fisheries council, which will then go to the council next week. I have nothing more introductory to say, I will pass the floor.
