Secondly, the government received information regarding Estonia's plan to become an observer state in the Arctic Council, one hundred and twenty days before the next summit, as decided last year. I informed the government that we intend to do this in the near future.
Preparations are underway and we plan to discuss this during the month of May in 2021.
We are, surprisingly, the northernmost, non-Arctic country and undoubtedly this is of interest to us in certain specific economic areas. Scientists also have their own strong geostrategic interests here, as do many of the world's major powers.
